UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1513
1 A RESOLUTION urging the Legislative Research Commission to direct the
2 Legislative Oversight and Investigations Committee to investigate the misuse of state
3 resources of the executive branch.
4 WHEREAS, Section 81 of the Constitution of Kentucky establishes that it is the
5 duty of the Governor to take care that the laws of this Commonwealth are faithfully
6 executed; and
7 WHEREAS, the Governor is a public servant of the citizens of this Commonwealth;
8 and
9 WHEREAS, under the administration of Governor Any Beshear, the Office of
10 Unemployment Insurance overpaid millions of dollars in fraudulent unemployment
11 benefits claims; and
12 WHEREAS, under the administration of Governor Andy Beshear, the Cabinet for
13 Health and Family Services failed to prevent at least $836 million dollars of Medicaid
14 program waste; and
15 WHEREAS, the Governor, under this administration, weaponized the Kentucky
16 Department of Alcoholic Beverage Control as a means to engage in targeted enforcement
17 and retaliation against Kentuckians for their criticisms of the Governor, in violation of the
18 First Amendment of the Constitution of the United States and Section 8 of the
19 Constitution of Kentucky; and
20 WHEREAS, the United States Court of Appeals for the Sixth Circuit denied this
21 Governor qualified immunity for his retaliatory conduct against Kentuckians in violation
22 of the First Amendment in Cooperrider v. Woods, 127 F.4th 1019 (6th Cir. 2025); and
23 WHEREAS, qualified immunity protects "all but the plainly incompetent or those
24 who knowingly violate the law," (Ashcroft v. Al-Kidd, 563 U.S. 731, 743 (2001) (quoting
25 Malley v. Briggs, 475 U.S. 335, 341 (1986)); and
26 WHEREAS, under the administration of Governor Andy Beshear, according to a
27 release from the United States Department of Justice, five Kentucky residents, including
Page 1 of 3
